{meta: title Just Out of Reach}
{meta: artist Patsy Cline}
{meta: writer Virgil F. Stewart}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Love that runs away from me
[D7]Dreams that just won't let me be
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Blues that keep on botherin' me
[G]Chains that just won't set me free
[C]Too far away from you and all your charms
[D7]Just out of reach of my two open [G]arms
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Each night in dreams I see your face
[D7]Memories time cannot erase
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
Then I awake and find you gone
[G]I'm so blue and all alone
[C]So far away from lips so sweet and warm
[D7]Just out of reach of my two open [G]arms
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
That lonesome feelin' all the time
[D7]Knowing you cannot be mine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
Dreams that hurt me in my sleep
[G]vows that we could never keep
[C]Too far away from lips so sweet and warm
[D7]Just out of reach of my two open [G]arms
{end_of_verse}
